results.lead_paragraph: WETHERBEE--Dana A. 82, of Huntington, former pilot for American Airlines, died peacefully. Born in NYC, WWII veteran, Distinguished Flying Cross, 13 Air Medals. Champlain College. Joined American Airlines 1948, retired 1983, as Director of Flight Eastern Region. Survived by Althea, wife of 55 years, children, James (only astronaut to command five space flights), Lawrence, Jule, Daniel, brother Donald and seven grandchildren.

results.lead_paragraph: Walking on the Moon 3D Opens today nationwide Directed by Mark Cowen Not rated; 40 minutes The producers of ''Magnificent Desolation: Walking on the Moon 3D'' either have very good luck in timing or very good friends in the space program. Their film opens at Imax theaters today, just four days after NASA's announcement that it plans to send astronauts back to the moon by 2018. (Readers may now take a moment to think about how old they will be then.)
